node.text:
It’s Baby Safety Month and we’re sharing our favorite tips to ensure your little one’s sleep space is as safe as possible. 

Swipe through to see the simple steps to remember when you lay your baby down for their nap or bedtime. 💤 Follow the link in our stories for a post full of tips for making your baby’s nursery safer.

Share these tips with a friend who might find them useful!

node.text:
How's your little one sleeping? 💤

Lead Parenting Expert & Safe Sleep Educator, Emily Osborne, shares her advice for parents tackling sleep regressions. A sleep regression is a change to your baby’s normal pattern of sleep that changes their ability to fall or stay asleep.

These are a few signs to watch out for but most importantly remember to be patient and know that this phase will soon pass for your little one. Follow the link in our stories to read more!
